#%% md
# SEO Meta Description Writer

## 1. Project Overview

**Task:** Generate SEO-optimized page titles (50-60 chars) and meta descriptions (150-160 chars) from page content and target keywords.

**Stack:** `LangChain` + `ChatOllama` + `qwen3.5:9b` — no API keys required.
#%% md
## 2. Learning Goals

| # | Skill |
|---|-------|
| 1 | **Generate** SEO titles and meta descriptions within character limits |
| 2 | **Include** target keywords naturally |
| 3 | **Create** click-compelling descriptions for search results |
| 4 | **Validate** outputs against Google guidelines |

## 3. Problem Statement

Every web page needs a title tag (50-60 chars) and meta description (150-160 chars) for search engines. Writing them manually for 100+ pages is tedious; LLMs can generate high-quality SEO metadata from page content.

## 4. Why This Matters

- **CTR impact** — well-written meta descriptions increase clicks 5-10%
- **Scale** — large sites have thousands of pages needing unique metadata
- **SEO ranking** — title tags are a confirmed ranking factor
#%% md
## 5. Setup
#%%
import os, json, re, time, warnings
os.environ["TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM"] = "false"
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

from langchain_ollama import ChatOllama
from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, SystemMessage

LLM_MODEL = "qwen3.5:9b"
llm = ChatOllama(model=LLM_MODEL, temperature=0.5)

def clean(text):
    if "<think>" in text: text = text.split("</think>")[-1].strip()
    return text.strip()

def ask(system, user):
    return clean(llm.invoke([SystemMessage(content=system), HumanMessage(content=user)]).content)

print(f"LLM ready: {ask('Reply with one word.', 'Say ready.')[:20]}")
#%% md
## 6. Page Data
#%%
PAGES = [
    {"url": "/learn-python-2025", "h1": "How to Learn Python in 2025", "keywords": ["learn Python", "Python tutorial"], "content": "A comprehensive guide to learning Python from scratch. Covers basics, data structures, functions, OOP, and real projects. Includes free resources and a 12-week roadmap.", "page_type": "blog"},
    {"url": "/best-laptops-data-science", "h1": "Best Laptops for Data Science", "keywords": ["data science laptop", "best laptop ML"], "content": "Comparison of top 10 laptops for data science. Tests cover RAM, GPU benchmarks for PyTorch/TensorFlow, battery life, and value. $1,000-$3,500.", "page_type": "listicle"},
    {"url": "/docker-beginners-guide", "h1": "Docker for Beginners", "keywords": ["Docker tutorial", "learn Docker"], "content": "Step-by-step Docker guide covering images, containers, volumes, networks, and Docker Compose. 5 hands-on exercises and production tips.", "page_type": "tutorial"},
    {"url": "/pricing", "h1": "CloudWorkspace Pricing", "keywords": ["CloudWorkspace pricing", "project management cost"], "content": "Free, Pro ($15/mo per user), Enterprise plans. Unlimited projects. Pro adds analytics, integrations, priority support.", "page_type": "landing"},
]
for p in PAGES:
    print(f"{p['url']:<35} [{p['page_type']}] Keywords: {', '.join(p['keywords'])}")
